. I just looked at the [OneSignal docs for notification icon customization](https://documentation.onesignal.com/v3.0/docs/customize-notification-icons), and it seems that all the sizes are actually wrong and the generation/copying of the large icon is missing as well. I was looking into fixing it, but two of the required sizes (24pxand256px) are not being generated byionic resources.. I ended up generating a white-only icon and usingsharp ` to generate the required sizes manually:
sh
cd hooks
npm install sharp
hooks/generate-onesignal-notification-icons-for-android.js:
```js
!/usr/bin/env node
const icon = 'icon.png';
const whiteIcon = 'icon-white.png';
// see:
//  * https://documentation.onesignal.com/v3.0/docs/customize-notification-icons
//  * https://ionicframework.com/docs/native/onesignal/
const { existsSync, mkdirSync } = require('fs');
const { resolve, join, dirname } = require('path');
const sharp = require('sharp');
const root = join(resolve(__dirname), '..');
const res = join(root, 'platforms', 'android', 'res');
const smallIcon = join(root, 'resources', 'android', whiteIcon);
const largeIcon = join(root, 'resources', 'android', icon);
const SMALL_ICON_NAME = 'ic_stat_onesignal_default.png';
const LARGE_ICON_NAME = 'ic_onesignal_large_icon_default.png';
const filesToCopy = [
  {
    // small icon - mdpi (24 px)
    size: 24,
    source: smallIcon,
    destination: join(res, 'drawable-mdpi', SMALL_ICON_NAME),
  },
  {
    // small icon - hdpi (36 px)
    size: 36,
    source: smallIcon,
    destination: join(res, 'drawable-hdpi', SMALL_ICON_NAME),
  },
  {
    // small icon - xhdpi (48 px)
    size: 48,
    source: smallIcon,
    destination: join(res, 'drawable-xhdpi', SMALL_ICON_NAME),
  },
  {
    // small icon - xxhdpi (72 px)
    size: 72,
    source: smallIcon,
    destination: join(res, 'drawable-xxhdpi', SMALL_ICON_NAME),
  },
  {
    // small icon - xxxhdpi (96 px)
    size: 96,
    source: smallIcon,
    destination: join(res, 'drawable-xxxhdpi', SMALL_ICON_NAME),
  },
  {
    // large icon - xxxhdpi (256 px)
    size: 256,
    source: largeIcon,
    destination: join(res, 'drawable-xxxhdpi', LARGE_ICON_NAME),
  },
];
for (const { size, source, destination } of filesToCopy) {
  if (existsSync(source) && !existsSync(destination)) {
    if (!existsSync(dirname(destination))) {
      mkdirSync(dirname(destination));
    }
sharp(source)
  .resize(size)
  .toFile(destination)
  .then(res => console.log(`onesignal icon generated (${res.width}px): ${destination}`))
  .catch(err => console.error(err));

}
}
```
